\code{\link[=summarize_db]{summarize_db()}}, \code{\link[=collect_db]{collect_db()}}) for the parts of the schema those functions don't
cover, and helpers for spatial (\code{\link[=filter_spatial_db]{filter_spatial_db()}}) and H3 hexagonal-indexing
(\code{\link[=h3_index_db]{h3_index_db()}}) operations.
}
\section{Getting started}{

Connect with \code{\link[=connect]{connect()}} (or a wrapper like \code{\link[=connect_opendata_local]{connect_opendata_local()}}) -- syncing a
local copy first with \code{\link[=sync_opendata]{sync_opendata()}}/\code{\link[=sync_opendata_cli]{sync_opendata_cli()}} is much faster than
streaming from S3 for anything beyond a quick look.
